# üõ°Ô∏è Web Vulnerability Scanner (GUI Based)

A Python-based Web Vulnerability Scanner with a Tkinter GUI that detects common web application vulnerabilities such as SQL Injection, Cross-Site Scripting (XSS), Open Redirect, and Directory Traversal.

This tool also demonstrates advanced conceptual modules like:
- VBE (Vulnerability Benchmark Evaluation)
- RSMSE (Risk Sensitive Mode Switching Engine)
- HSE (Hybrid Scanner Engine)

---

## üöÄ Features

- GUI interface using Tkinter
- SQL Injection detection using payload injection
- XSS vulnerability detection
- Open Redirect vulnerability check
- Directory Traversal detection
- Risk evaluation and secure mode switching
- Benchmark evaluation simulation (OWASP/WAVSEP inspired)
- Hybrid scanning simulation (SAST + DAST + Fuzzing concept)
- Export scan results as a report file

---

## üß∞ Tech Stack

- Python 3.x
- Tkinter (GUI)
- Requests library (HTTP handling)
